3c29-ad7e-4ec4-9f21-90b740fc9bdd\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/dip/Repositories/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a2ab7252-7768-4152-a6fc-401dad1b707d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"feat/trails\",\"slug\":\"sorted-dazzling-globe\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01ECCPeDTMJC8HwPZAfUWjpj\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Trails Implementation\\n     2→\\n     3→## Overview\\n     4→\\n     5→Branch-centric work tracking system called \\\"Trails\\\" that replaces PR-based task tracking. Trails use pure git primitives (branches, commits) rather than GitHub-specific features (PRs/Issues).\\n     6→\\n     7→**Key decisions:**\\n     8→- Store trail metadata in `entire/trails/v1` orphan branch (similar to checkpoints in `entire/checkpoints/v1`)\\n     9→- One trail per branch — trail tracks the full lifecycle of work on that branch\\n    10→- Link to checkpoints via explicit `checkpoints.json` (resilient to branch renames)\\n    11→- Support discussion/comments stored alongside trail metadata\\n    12→- No dependency on GitHub PRs — PR info is optional/supplementary\\n    13→- No database table yet — trails are read/written directly via GitHub git API\\n    14→\\n    15→## Concepts\\n    16→\\n    17→### Trail Lifecycle\\n    18→\\n    19→```\\n    20→draft → open → in_progress → in_review → merged / closed\\n    21→```\\n    22→\\n    23→- `merged` is set automatically when the trail's feature branch is fully merged into its base branch (detected via push webhook)\\n    24→- `closed` means abandoned/cancelled without merge\\n    25→\\n    26→### Relationship Model\\n    27→\\n    28→```\\n    29→Trail (1) ←──branch──→ (many) Checkpoints\\n    30→   │                         │\\n    31→   └── \\\"why/what\\\"            └── \\\"how/when\\\"\\n    32→       (human intent)            (machine snapshots)\\n    33→```\\n    34→\\n    35→- **Trail**: Human-defined work item tracking purpose and status\\n    36→- **Checkpoint**: Machine-generated snapshot of work at a commit\\n    37→- **Link**: Explicit `checkpoints.json` file in each trail folder\\n    38→\\n    39→## Storage Format\\n    40→\\n    41→### Branch Structure\\n    42→\\n    43→```\\n    44→entire/trails/v1 (branch)\\n    45→├── .gitkeep\\n    46→├── ab/\\n    47→│   └── cdef1234/              # trail_id = \\\"abcdef1234\\\"\\n    48→│       ├── metadata.json      # Trail metadata\\n    49→│       ├── discussion.json    # Comments/threads\\n    50→│       └── checkpoints.json   # References to checkpoints\\n    51→```\\n    52→\\n    53→### metadata.json\\n    54→\\n    55→```json\\n    56→{\\n    57→  \\\"trail_id\\\": \\\"abcdef1234\\\",\\n    58→  \\\"branch\\\": \\\"dipree/add-auth\\\",\\n    59→  \\\"base\\\": \\\"main\\\",\\n    60→  \\\"title\\\": \\\"Add user authentication\\\",\\n    61→  \\\"body\\\": \\\"OAuth2 with GitHub provider\\\",\\n    62→  \\\"status\\\": \\\"in_progress\\\",\\n    63→  \\\"author\\\": \\\"dipree\\\",\\n    64→  \\\"assignees\\\": [\\\"dipree\\\"],\\n    65→  \\\"labels\\\": [\\\"security\\\"],\\n    66→  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-02-18T10:30:00Z\\\",\\n    67→  \\\"updated_at\\\": \\\"2026-02-20T14:22:00Z\\\",\\n    68→  \\\"merged_at\\\": null\\n    69→}\\n    70→```\\n    71→\\n    72→### discussion.json\\n    73→\\n    74→```json\\n    75→{\\n    76→  \\\"comments\\\": [\\n    77→    {\\n    78→      \\\"id\\\": \\\"c1\\\",\\n    79→      \\\"author\\\": \\\"reviewer\\\",\\n    80→      \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-02-20T10:00:00Z\\\",\\n    81→      \\\"body\\\": \\\"Should we use refresh tokens?\\\",\\n    82→      \\\"resolved\\\": false,\\n    83→      \\\"resolved_by\\\": null,\\n    84→      \\\"resolved_at\\\": null,\\n    85→      \\\"replies\\\": [\\n    86→        {\\n    87→          \\\"id\\\": \\\"c1r1\\\",\\n    88→          \\\"author\\\": \\\"dipree\\\",\\n    89→          \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-02-20T10:15:00Z\\\",\\n    90→          \\\"body\\\": \\\"Yes, added in latest commit\\\"\\n    91→        }\\n    92→      ]\\n    93→    }\\n    94→  ]\\n    95→}\\n    96→```\\n    97→\\n    98→### checkpoints.json\\n    99→\\n   100→```json\\n   101→{\\n   102→  \\\"checkpoints\\\": [\\n   103→    {\\n   104→      \\\"checkpoint_id\\\": \\\"xyz789\\\",\\n   105→      \\\"commit_sha\\\": \\\"abc123def456\\\",\\n   106→      \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-02-19T15:00:00Z\\\",\\n   107→      \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Implemented OAuth flow\\\"\\n   108→    }\\n   109→  ]\\n   110→}\\n   111→```\\n   112→\\n   113→## Implementation\\n   114→\\n   115→### API Routes (`src/routes/cache.ts`)\\n   116→\\n   117→All trail endpoints are under the repo-scoped cache router:\\n   118→\\n   119→| Method | Path | Description |\\n   120→|--------|------|-------------|\\n   121→| `GET` | `/:org/:repo/trails` | List all trails |\\n   122→| `GET` | `/:org/:repo/trails/:trailId` | Get trail with checkpoints |\\n   123→| `POST` | `/:org/:repo/trails` | Create new trail |\\n   124→| `PATCH` | `/:org/:repo/trails/:trailId` | Update trail metadata |\\n   125→| `POST` | `/:org/:repo/trails/:trailId/comments` | Add comment |\\n   126→\\n   127→### GitHub Operations (`src/lib/github.ts`)\\n   128→\\n   129→- `discoverTrailsFromBranch()` — List trail IDs from branch directory structure\\n   130→- `fetchTrailDataBatch()` — Batch-fetch metadata/discussion/checkpoints via GraphQL\\n   131→- `commitTrailFiles()` — Commit trail files to `entire/trails/v1` branch\\n   132→- `ensureTrailsBranchExists()` — Create orphan branch if needed\\n   133→- `createBranchIfNotExists()` — Create feature branch from base\\n   134→- `updateTrailFile()` — Update a single file in a trail folder\\n   135→- `isBranchMergedInto()` — Check if a branch is fully merged via compare API\\n   136→\\n   137→### Webhook Integration (`src/lib/webhook/processing.ts`)\\n   138→\\n   139→- **Push events**: When a push lands on a base branch, check if any trail targeting that base has been fully merged (`ahead_by === 0` from compare API). If so, auto-transition to `merged` status.\\n   140→- **Checkpoint linking**: When checkpoints are created, `linkCheckpointsToTrails()` finds matching trails by branch name and updates their `checkpoints.json`.\\n   141→\\n   142→### Frontend\\n   143→\\n   144→- **TrailsPage** (`frontend/src/domains/platform/trails/pages/TrailsPage.tsx`) — List view with status tabs, filtering, search\\n   145→- **TrailDetailPage** (`frontend/src/domains/platform/trails/pages/TrailDetailPage.tsx`) — Detail view with discussion, checkpoints, metadata editing\\n   146→- **CreateTrailDialog** (`frontend/src/domains/platform/trails/components/CreateTrailDialog.tsx`) — Modal for creating new trails with auto-generated branch names\\n   147→\\n   148→### Database\\n   149→\\n   150→No database table exists yet. Trail data is read/written directly via GitHub's git API. The `repo-sync-service.ts` has forward-looking sync code (guarded by `if (!db.trails) return`) for when a `repo_trails` table is eventually created in PlanetScale.\\n   151→\\n   152→## Files\\n   153→\\n   154→| File | Purpose |\\n   155→|------|---------|\\n   156→| `api/src/routes/cache.ts` | Trail API endpoints |\\n   157→| `api/src/lib/github.ts` | Trail git operations |\\n   158→| `api/src/lib/webhook/processing.ts` | Merge detection, checkpoint linking |\\n   159→| `api/src/lib/repo-sync-service.ts` | Trail sync (DB upsert, currently no-op) |\\n   160→| `api/src/types.ts` | `TrailMetadata`, `TrailStatus`, `Trail`, etc. |\\n   161→| `frontend/src/domains/platform/trails/` | Frontend pages, API client, hooks |\\n   162→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"ed4fbdda-bc5c-482e-8966-727f2afd5d10\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T13:14:45.101Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aa2534f5b6b35c625\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_013TM3nuFakJoivvpjRMyjf6\",\"paren